This guide explains what a shutter page is and when you would need to use it for your service.

## What are shutter pages
Shutter pages are used to keep users out of a service when the service is unavailable for:

* maintenance – planned
* technical problem – unplanned
* closed - the end of a filing window
* closed forever
* not avalible yet

All HMRC services should have a shutter page.

## General

All pages, no matter what type, should:

* have the service title in the top bar as it appears throughout the service
* avoid alpha or beta banners
* avoid breadcrumbs
* use the H1 and page title "Service unavailable"
* be clear and concise without using colour or language that may alarm or confuse people, like red text or phrases like private beta

